{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775879498819,"sessionID":"ses_28555b7a2ffeGBXkhsrK5EVtx7","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaaac2c0014H15V1eMNYBOzn","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7aaa8cb9001BcWaulU5aEJvN0","sessionID":"ses_28555b7a2ffeGBXkhsrK5EVtx7","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":28310,"input":12971,"output":236,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15103}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775879503878,"sessionID":"ses_28555b7a2ffeGBXkhsrK5EVtx7","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaac0030013LdT4TKTt5QdxX","messageID":"msg_d7aaaac5b001W5pnNUrhTa8nHF","sessionID":"ses_28555b7a2ffeGBXkhsrK5EVtx7","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879508715,"sessionID":"ses_28555b7a2ffeGBXkhsrK5EVtx7","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaad2c6001Z2ZnHNkM4OQRxX","messageID":"msg_d7aaaac5b001W5pnNUrhTa8nHF","sessionID":"ses_28555b7a2ffeGBXkhsrK5EVtx7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-416683858281415385cd129399382994","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020: CLI pack 命令 — Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: The `pack` command in the AgentCube CLI is responsible for validating and preparing an agent workspace, merging CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generating a `Dockerfile`, and reporting paths to the packaged artifacts.\n6: \n7: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n8: **Language:** Python  \n9: **Source Root:** `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`\n10: \n11: ## Architecture\n12: \n13: ### Components\n14: \n15: | Component | Location | Responsibility |\n16: |-----------|----------|----------------|\n17: | `PackRuntime` | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packing logic implementation |\n18: | `MetadataService` | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata loading, saving, and validation |\n19: | `MetadataOptions` | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Dataclass for CLI option parsing |\n20: | `pack` command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command definition and CLI entry point |\n21: \n22: ### Data Flow\n23: \n24: ```\n25: CLI Options → MetadataOptions → PackRuntime.pack()\n26:                                       ↓\n27:                      _validate_workspace_structure()\n28:                                       ↓\n29:                       _load_or_create_metadata()\n30:                                       ↓\n31:                       _apply_option_overrides()\n32:                                       ↓\n33:                     _validate_language_compatibility()\n34:                                       ↓\n35:                          _process_dependencies()\n36:                                       ↓\n37:                          _generate_dockerfile()\n38:                                       ↓\n39:                      _update_pack_metadata()\n40:                                       ↓\n41:                          _prepare_output_path()\n42:                                       ↓\n43:                             Return result\n44: ```\n45: \n46: ## Detailed Implementation\n47: \n48: ### 1. CLI Command (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n49: \n50: ```python\n51: def pack(\n52:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n53:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n54:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n55:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n56:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n57:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n58:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n59:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n60:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n61: ) -> None:\n62:     \"\"\"Package an agent workspace by validating structure and generating metadata.\"\"\"\n63: ```\n64: \n65: **Command behavior:**\n66: - Resolves workspace path relative to current directory if not absolute\n67: - Creates `PackRuntime` instance with verbose flag\n68: - Collects options into a dictionary\n69: - Calls `PackRuntime.pack(workspace_path, **options)`\n70: - Handles exceptions via `_handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)`\n71: \n72: ### 2. PackRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n73: \n74: #### Class Structure\n75: \n76: ```python\n77: class PackRuntime:\n78:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n79:         self.verbose = verbose\n80:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n81: ```\n82: \n83: #### Main Method: `pack()`\n84: \n85: ```python\n86: def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n87:     \"\"\"Package an agent workspace.\n88: \n89:     Returns:\n90:         Dict containing:\n91:         - agent_name: str\n92:         - workspace_path: str (absolute path)\n93:         - metadata_path: str\n94:         - dockerfile_path: Optional[str]\n95:         - language: str\n96:         - entrypoint: str\n97:         - port: int\n98:     \"\"\"\n99:     with Progress() as progress:\n100:         task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Packing workspace...\", total=100)\n101: \n102:         progress.update(task, advance=10)\n103:         self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n104: \n105:         progress.update(task, advance=20)\n106:         metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n107: \n108:         progress.update(task, advance=20)\n109:         metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n110: \n111:         progress.update(task, advance=10)\n112:         self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n113: \n114:         progress.update(task, advance=15)\n115:         self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n116: \n117:         progress.update(task, advance=15)\n118:         dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n119: \n120:         progress.update(task, advance=10)\n121:         self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n122: \n123:         progress.update(task, advance=10)\n124:         output_path = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n125: \n126:     return {\n127:         \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n128:         \"workspace_path\": str(output_path),\n129:         \"metadata_path\": str(output_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n130:         \"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path) if dockerfile_path else None,\n131:         \"language\": metadata.language,\n132:         \"entrypoint\": metadata.entrypoint,\n133:         \"port\": metadata.port,\n134:     }\n135: ```\n136: \n137: #### Helper Methods\n138: \n139: **`_validate_workspace_structure()`**\n140: - Validates `workspace_path` exists and is a directory\n141: - Raises `ValueError` with clear message if not\n142: \n143: **`_load_or_create_metadata()`**\n144: - Attempts to load existing metadata from `agent_metadata.yaml`\n145: - Falls back to `agent.yaml` then `metadata.yaml` if primary missing\n146: - Creates new `AgentMetadata` if no existing file found\n147: - Infers defaults: `language=\"python\"`, `port=8080`, `build_mode=\"local\"`\n148: \n149: **`_apply_option_overrides()`**\n150: - Merges CLI options into metadata\n151: - Priority: CLI options > existing metadata > defaults\n152: - Creates new `AgentMetadata` instance to ensure validation\n153: \n154: **`_validate_language_compatibility()`**\n155: - Validates Python workspace: requires at least one `*.py` file\n156: - Validates Java workspace: requires `pom.xml` file\n157: - Raises `ValueError` with specific message per language\n158: \n159: **`_process_dependencies()`**\n160: - Python: Validates `requirements.txt` exists, creates if missing with minimal content\n161: - Java: Validates `pom.xml` exists (already checked in compatibility)\n162: \n163: **`_generate_dockerfile()`**\n164: - Skips if `metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\"`\n165: - Calls language-specific generator based on `metadata.language`\n166: - Returns path to generated Dockerfile or None\n167: \n168: **`_generate_python_dockerfile()`**\n169: - Base image: `python:3.11-slim`\n170: - Workdir: `/app`\n171: - Copy requirements and install\n172: - Copy application code\n173: - Expose port from metadata\n174: - Entrypoint from metadata\n175: \n176: **`_generate_java_dockerfile()`**\n177: - Base image: `openjdk:17-jdk-slim`\n178: - Workdir: `/app`\n179: - Copy `pom.xml` and run Maven build\n180: - Copy JAR from target\n181: - Expose port from metadata\n182: - Entrypoint: `java -jar {jar_name}`\n183: \n184: **`_update_pack_metadata()`**\n185: - Saves metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml` using `MetadataService`\n186: - Excludes None fields from output\n187: - Updates dockerfile_path in metadata\n188: \n189: **`_prepare_output_path()`**\n190: - Returns workspace_path if output not specified\n191: - Creates output directory if doesn't exist\n192: - Returns absolute path\n193: \n194: **`_infer_entrypoint()`**\n195: - Python: `python main.py` if `main.py` exists\n196: - Java: `java -jar target/*.jar`\n197: - Default: metadata.entrpoint or raise error\n198: \n199: ### 3. MetadataService (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n200: \n201: ```python\n202: class MetadataService:\n203:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n204:         self.verbose = verbose\n205:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n206: \n207:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n208:         \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace with fallback order.\"\"\"\n209:         for filename in [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]:\n210:             metadata_path = workspace_path / filename\n211:             if metadata_path.exists():\n212:                 with open(metadata_path, \"r\") as f:\n213:                     data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n214:                 return AgentMetadata(**data)\n215:         raise FileNotFoundError(\"No metadata file found in workspace\")\n216: \n217:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n218:         \"\"\"Save metadata to agent_metadata.yaml.\"\"\"\n219:         metadata_path = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n220:         with open(metadata_path, \"w\") as f:\n221:             yaml.dump(\n222:                 metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True),\n223:                 f,\n224:                 default_flow_style=False,\n225:                 indent=2,\n226:                 sort_keys=False,\n227:             )\n228: \n229:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n230:         \"\"\"Validate workspace structure based on language.\"\"\"\n231:         metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n232:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n233:             self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n234:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n235:             self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n236:         return True\n237: \n238:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n239:         \"\"\"Validate Python workspace has at least one .py file.\"\"\"\n240:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n241:         if not py_files:\n242:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n243: \n244:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n245:         \"\"\"Validate Java workspace has pom.xml.\"\"\"\n246:         if not (workspace_path / \"pom.xml\").exists():\n247:             raise ValueError(\"Java workspace requires pom.xml\")\n248: ```\n249: \n250: ### 4. MetadataOptions (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n251: \n252: ```python\n253: @dataclass\n254: class MetadataOptions:\n255:     \"\"\"Options for pack command CLI arguments.\"\"\"\n256:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n257:     language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n258:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n259:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n260:     build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n261:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n262:     description: Optional[str] = None\n263:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n264:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n265:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n266:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n267:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n268:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n269:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n270:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n271: \n272:     @classmethod\n273:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n274:         \"\"\"Create from CLI options dict.\"\"\"\n275:         return cls(\n276:             agent_name=options.get(\"agent_name\"),\n277:             language=options.get(\"language\"),\n278:             entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\"),\n279:             port=options.get(\"port\"),\n280:             build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\"),\n281:             description=options.get(\"description\"),\n282:             workspace_manager_url=options.get(\"workspace_manager_url\"),\n283:             router_url=options.get(\"router_url\"),\n284:             readiness_probe_path=options.get(\"readiness_probe_path\"),\n285:             readiness_probe_port=options.get(\"readiness_probe_port\"),\n286:         )\n287: ```\n288: \n289: ### 5. AgentMetadata (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n290: \n291: ```python\n292: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n293:     \"\"\"Agent metadata model with validation.\"\"\"\n294:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n295:     description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n296:     language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n297:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n298:     port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n299:     build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n300:     region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n301:     version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n302:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n303:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n304:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n305:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n306:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n307:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n308:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n309:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n310:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n311:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n312:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n313:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n314:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n315:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n316: \n317:     @field_validator(\"language\")\n318:     @classmethod\n319:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n320:         \"\"\"Validate language is supported.\"\"\"\n321:         v = v.lower()\n322:         if v not in [\"python\", \"java\"]:\n323:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {v}. Supported: python, java\")\n324:         return v\n325: \n326:     @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n327:     @classmethod\n328:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n329:         \"\"\"Validate build mode is supported.\"\"\"\n330:         v = v.lower()\n331:         if v not in [\"local\", \"cloud\"]:\n332:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build mode: {v}. Supported: local, cloud\")\n333:         return v\n334: \n335:     @field_validator(\"port\")\n336:     @classmethod\n337:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n338:         \"\"\"Validate port is in valid range.\"\"\"\n339:         if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n340:             raise ValueError(f\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\")\n341:         return v\n342: ```\n343: \n344: ## Error Handling\n345: \n346: ### Error Flow\n347: \n348: ```python\n349: try:\n350:     result = runtime.pack(workspace_path, **options)\n351:     # Print success with Rich console\n352:     console.print(f\"[green]✓[/green] Agent packed successfully: {result['agent_name']}\")\n353:     console.print(f\"  Workspace: [cyan]{result['workspace_path']}[/cyan]\")\n354:     console.print(f\"  Metadata: [cyan]{result['metadata_path']}[/cyan]\")\n355:     if result['dockerfile_path']:\n356:         console.print(f\"  Dockerfile: [cyan]{result['dockerfile_path']}[/cyan]\")\n357: except Exception as e:\n358:     _handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)\n359: ```\n360: \n361: ### `_handle_error()` Implementation\n362: \n363: ```python\n364: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n365:     \"\"\"Handle command errors with optional traceback.\"\"\"\n366:     console = Console()\n367:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}:[/red] {e}\")\n368:     if verbose:\n369:         import traceback\n370:         console.print(traceback.format_exc())\n371:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n372: ```\n373: \n374: ### Common Error Scenarios\n375: \n376: | Error | Condition | Message |\n377: |-------|-----------|---------|\n378: | `ValueError` | Workspace doesn't exist | \"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\" |\n379: | `ValueError` | No Python files | \"No Python files found in workspace\" |\n380: | `ValueError` | No pom.xml for Java | \"Java workspace requires pom.xml\" |\n381: | `ValueError` | Invalid language | \"Unsupported language: {lang}. Supported: python, java\" |\n382: | `ValueError` | Invalid build mode | \"Unsupported build mode: {mode}. Supported: local, cloud\" |\n383: | `ValueError` | Invalid port | \"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {port}\" |\n384: | `PydanticValidationError` | Invalid metadata type | Validation errors from Pydantic |\n385: \n386: ## CLI Output Format\n387: \n388: ### Success Output\n389: \n390: ```\n391: ✓ Agent packed successfully: my-agent\n392:   Workspace: /path/to/workspace\n393:   Metadata: /path/to/workspace/agent_metadata.yaml\n394:   Dockerfile: /path/to/workspace/Dockerfile\n395: ```\n396: \n397: ### Error Output (non-verbose)\n398: \n399: ```\n400: Error pack: No Python files found in workspace\n401: ```\n402: \n403: ### Error Output (verbose)\n404: \n405: ```\n406: Error pack: No Python files found in workspace\n407: Traceback (most recent call last):\n408:   File \"...\", line ..., in pack\n409:     self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path)\n410:   ...\n411: ```\n412: \n413: ## Dependencies\n414: \n415: ### Runtime Dependencies (from `pyproject.toml`)\n416: \n417: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0` - CLI framework\n418: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` - Data validation\n419: - `pyyaml>=6.0` - YAML parsing/writing\n420: - `rich>=13.0.0` - Terminal output formatting\n421: \n422: ### Optional Dependencies\n423: \n424: - `docker>=6.0.0` - Used by `DockerService` (not in pack command)\n425: \n426: ## Test Coverage\n427: \n428: ### Unit Tests Required\n429: \n430: | Component | Test Cases |\n431: |-----------|------------|\n432: | `PackRuntime.pack()` | - Happy path with valid workspace<br>- Workspace validation failure<br>- Metadata loading fallback<br>- Option override merging<br>- Language-specific validation<br>- Dockerfile generation |\n433: | `_validate_workspace_structure()` | - Existing directory<br>- Non-existent path<br>- File instead of directory |\n434: | `_load_or_create_metadata()` | - Load existing metadata<br>- Fallback to agent.yaml<br>- Fallback to metadata.yaml<br>- Create new metadata<br>- Infer defaults |\n435: | `_apply_option_overrides()` | - Override all fields<br>- Partial override<br>- No override |\n436: | `_validate_language_compatibility()` | - Valid Python workspace<br>- Python workspace with no .py files<br>- Valid Java workspace<br>- Java workspace without pom.xml |\n437: | `_generate_dockerfile()` | - Python local build<br>- Java local build<br>- Cloud build (skip) |\n438: | `MetadataService` | - Load metadata from all filenames<br>- Save metadata with exclude_none<br>- Validate workspace per language |\n439: \n440: ### Integration Tests\n441: \n442: - End-to-end pack command with workspace\n443: - CLI option parsing and passing\n444: - Error handling flow\n445: \n446: ## Security Considerations\n447: \n448: 1. **Path validation**: Ensure workspace path is within expected directory to prevent path traversal\n449: 2. **Dockerfile generation**: Validate port range to prevent invalid container configuration\n450: 3. **Metadata persistence**: Exclude sensitive fields (auth tokens) from saved metadata if not needed\n451: 4. **Command injection**: Validate and sanitize entrypoint command before writing to Dockerfile\n452: \n453: ## Future Enhancements\n454: \n455: 1. Support for additional languages (Node.js, Go, etc.)\n456: 2. Multi-stage Dockerfile generation for optimized images\n457: 3. Dependency analysis to include only required packages\n458: 4. Workspace templates for quick-start\n459: 5. Interactive mode for metadata creation\n460: 6. Workspace validation rules extensible via plugins\n\n(End of file - total 460 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020: CLI pack 命令 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `pack` command in the AgentCube CLI is responsible for validating and preparing an agent workspace, merging CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generating a `Dockerfile`, and reporting paths to the packaged artifacts.\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Source Root:** `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n| Component | Location | Responsibility |\n|-----------|----------|----------------|\n| `PackRuntime` | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packing logic implementation |\n| `MetadataService` | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata loading, saving, and validation |\n| `MetadataOptions` | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Dataclass for CLI option parsing |\n| `pack` command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command definition and CLI entry point |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775879508703,"end":1775879508712}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775879508740,"sessionID":"ses_28555b7a2ffeGBXkhsrK5EVtx7","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaad2ea001Pcqq1vUV59uW6H","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7aaaac5b001W5pnNUrhTa8nHF","sessionID":"ses_28555b7a2ffeGBXkhsrK5EVtx7","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":28620,"input":13277,"output":303,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15040}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775879514603,"sessionID":"ses_28555b7a2ffeGBXkhsrK5EVtx7","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaae9e9001XsFrEVFBOYw1zP","messageID":"msg_d7aaad31d001F1SfLqCXw4gQLX","sessionID":"ses_28555b7a2ffeGBXkhsrK5EVtx7","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879631096,"sessionID":"ses_28555b7a2ffeGBXkhsrK5EVtx7","part":{"id":"prt_d7aacb010001edEW7O6lvUR5AD","messageID":"msg_d7aaad31d001F1SfLqCXw4gQLX","sessionID":"ses_28555b7a2ffeGBXkhsrK5EVtx7","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-2975c7214ff74aebb4b2e5e845c1c887","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe SDK HTTP 底层客户端 provides the foundational HTTP client infrastructure for the AgentCube Python SDK, enabling communication with the Workload Manager (control plane) and Router (data plane) for Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime services.\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Source Root:** `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`  \n**Size:** M\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n| Component | Location | Responsibility |\n|-----------|----------|----------------|\n| `create_session` | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | Creates pooled requests.Session with HTTPAdapter |\n| `read_token_from_file` | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Reads authentication token from file |\n| `get_logger` | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | Provides configured logger instances |\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | HTTP client for Workload Manager API |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | HTTP client for Code Interpreter Router API |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | HTTP client for Agent Runtime Router API |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | High-level Code Interpreter client |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | High-level Agent Runtime client |\n\n### Data Flow\n\n```\nControl Plane Flow:\nControlPlaneClient → requests.Session → Workload Manager API\n                       ↓\n                  Connection Pooling\n                  HTTPAdapter (http/https)\n\nData Plane Flow (Code Interpreter):\nCodeInterpreterClient → CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient → requests.Session → Router API\n                                                           ↓\n                                                      Connection Pooling\n                                                      HTTPAdapter (http/https)\n\nData Plane Flow (Agent Runtime):\nAgentRuntimeClient → AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient → requests.Session → Router API\n                                                         ↓\n                                                    Connection Pooling\n                                                    HTTPAdapter (http/https)\n```\n\n## Package Structure\n\n```\nagentcube-sdk/\n├── pyproject.toml                    # Package metadata and dependencies\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                   # Public API exports\n│   ├── code_interpreter.py           # CodeInterpreterClient\n│   ├── agent_runtime.py              # AgentRuntimeClient\n│   ├── exceptions.py                 # Exception hierarchy\n│   ├── clients/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py              # Client re-exports\n│   │   ├── control_plane.py         # ControlPlaneClient\n│   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n│   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n│   └── utils/\n│       ├── __init__.py              # Module marker\n│       ├── http.py                  # create_session\n│       ├── utils.py                 # read_token_from_file\n│       └── log.py                   # get_logger\n```\n\n## Detailed Implementation\n\n### 1. HTTP Session Management (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n\n```python\ndef create_session(\n    pool_connections: int = 10,\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n) -> requests.Session:\n    \"\"\"Create a requests.Session with connection pooling.\n\n    Args:\n        pool_connections: Number of connection pools to cache\n        pool_maxsize: Maximum number of connections in pool\n\n    Returns:\n        Configured requests.Session with HTTPAdapter mounted\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n- Creates `requests.Session` instance\n- Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` schemes\n- Configures connection pooling with specified parameters\n- Returns session ready for use\n\n**Connection Pooling Benefits:**\n- Reuses TCP connections for multiple requests to same host\n- Reduces latency from TCP handshake and TLS negotiation\n- Limits resource usage with pool size constraints\n\n### 2. Token Management (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n\n```python\ndef read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Read authentication token from file.\n\n    Args:\n        file_path: Path to token file (e.g., K8s service account token)\n\n    Returns:\n        Token string stripped of whitespace\n\n    Note:\n        Returns empty string on FileNotFoundError to support\n        optional authentication scenarios\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n- Opens and reads file contents\n- Strips whitespace from token\n- Returns empty string if file not found (graceful degradation)\n- Used for Kubernetes service account token: `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n\n### 3. Logger Configuration (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n\n```python\ndef get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n    \"\"\"Get configured logger instance.\n\n    Args:\n        name: Logger name (typically __name__)\n        level: Logging level (default: logging.INFO)\n\n    Returns:\n        Configured logger instance\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n- Creates or retrieves logger by name\n- Sets specified logging level\n- Returns logger ready for use\n- Supports both integer and string level specifications\n\n### 4. ControlPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n\n#### Class Structure\n\n```python\nclass ControlPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ):\n        \"\"\"Initialize control plane client.\n\n        Args:\n            workload_manager_url: Base URL for Workload Manager API\n                                  (defaults to WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var)\n            auth_token: Authentication token (defaults to SA token file)\n            timeout: Read timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n            connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n            pool_connections: Connection pool size (default: 10)\n            pool_maxsize: Max connections per pool (default: 10)\n        \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Initialization Logic:**\n1. Resolve `workload_manager_url` from parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable\n2. Resolve `auth_token` from parameter or service account token file\n3. Store timeout configuration\n4. Create session with connection pooling\n5. Configure default headers: `Content-Type: application/json`\n6. If token present, set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header\n\n#### Session Creation\n\n```python\ndef create_session(\n    name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n    namespace: str = \"default\",\n    metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n    ttl: int = 3600,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Create a new Code Interpreter session.\n\n    Args:\n        name: Session name\n        namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n        metadata: Optional metadata dictionary\n        ttl: Time-to-live in seconds (default: 3600)\n\n    Returns:\n        Session ID string\n\n    Raises:\n        ValueError: If sessionId not in response\n        requests.exceptions.RequestException: On HTTP errors\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**HTTP Details:**\n- **Method:** `POST`\n- **Path:** `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`\n- **Headers:** `Content-Type: application/json`, `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token)\n- **Body:** JSON `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}`\n- **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n- **Response:** JSON with `sessionId` field\n\n#### Session Deletion\n\n```python\ndef delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Delete a Code Interpreter session.\n\n    Args:\n        session_id: Session ID to delete\n\n    Returns:\n        True if deletion succeeded (including 404), False otherwise\n\n    Note:\n        404 responses are treated as success (idempotent delete)\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**HTTP Details:**\n- **Method:** `DELETE`\n- **Path:** `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n- **Headers:** Same as session creation\n- **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n- **Response Handling:**\n  - Returns `True` on 200, 404 (not found considered success)\n  - Returns `False` on other errors\n  - Logs errors before returning\n\n#### Cleanup\n\n```python\ndef close(self) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Close the HTTP session and release resources.\"\"\"\n    self.session.close()\n```\n\n### 5. CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n\n#### Class Structure\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n        cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n        base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ):\n        \"\"\"Initialize Code Interpreter data plane client.\n\n        Args:\n            session_id: Session ID for header\n            router_url: Router base URL (used if base_url not provided)\n            namespace: Namespace for URL construction\n            cr_name: Custom resource name for URL construction\n            base_url: Full base URL (overrides URL construction)\n            timeout: Read timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n            connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n            pool_connections: Connection pool size (default: 10)\n            pool_maxsize: Max connections per pool (default: 10)\n        \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Base URL Resolution:**\n```python\nif base_url is None:\n    base_path = \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n    self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\nelse:\n    self.base_url = base_url\n```\n\n**Session Configuration:**\n- Creates session with connection pooling\n- Sets default header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n\n#### Request Helper\n\n```python\ndef _request(\n    self,\n    method: str,\n    endpoint: str,\n    body: Optional[bytes] = None,\n    **kwargs\n) -> requests.Response:\n    \"\"\"Execute HTTP request with session header.\n\n    Args:\n        method: HTTP method (GET, POST, etc.)\n        endpoint: Relative path to base_url\n        body: Optional request body as bytes\n        **kwargs: Additional arguments for requests.request\n\n    Returns:\n        requests.Response object\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Implementation:**\n- Constructs full URL: `urljoin(self.base_url, endpoint)`\n- Includes session header automatically\n- Sets `Content-Type: application/json` if body provided\n- Uses timeout: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n- Passes through additional kwargs to requests\n\n#### Command Execution\n\n```python\ndef execute_command(\n    self,\n    command: Union[str, List[str]],\n    timeout: Optional[float] = None\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Execute command in Code Interpreter session.\n\n    Args:\n        command: Command string or list of arguments\n        timeout: Command timeout in seconds (None for default)\n\n    Returns:\n        Command stdout output\n\n    Raises:\n        CommandExecutionError: If command exits with non-zero code\n        requests.exceptions.RequestException: On HTTP errors\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**HTTP Details:**\n- **Method:** `POST`\n- **Path:** `api/execute`\n- **Headers:** `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n- **Body:** JSON `{\"command\": [arg1, arg2, ...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}`\n- **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout_value + 2.0)` (buffer for PicoD exit 124)\n- **Response Processing:**\n  - Parse JSON response\n  - Check `exit_code` field\n  - Raise `CommandExecutionError` if non-zero\n  - Return `stdout` on success\n\n#### File Operations\n\n**Write File:**\n```python\ndef write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Write content to remote file.\n\n    Args:\n        content: File content as string\n        remote_path: Remote file path\n\n    Raises:\n        DataPlaneError: On write failure\n    \"\"\"\n```\n- **Method:** `POST`\n- **Path:** `api/files`\n- **Headers:** `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n- **Body:** JSON `{\"path\": remote_path, \"content\": base64(content), \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n\n**Upload File:**\n```python\ndef upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Upload local file to remote path.\n\n    Args:\n        local_path: Local file path\n        remote_path: Remote file path\n\n    Raises:\n        FileNotFoundError: If local file doesn't exist\n        DataPlaneError: On upload failure\n    \"\"\"\n```\n- **Method:** `POST`\n- **Path:** `api/files`\n- **Headers:** `x-agentcube-session-id` (explicitly set, no JSON Content-Type)\n- **Body:** Multipart form data\n  - `files`: `{'file': (filename, file_handle)}`\n  - `data`: `{'path': remote_path, 'mode': '0644'}`\n\n**Download File:**\n```python\ndef download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Download remote file to local path.\n\n    Args:\n        remote_path: Remote file path\n        local_path: Local file path\n\n    Raises:\n        DataPlaneError: On download failure\n    \"\"\"\n```\n- **Method:** `GET`\n- **Path:** `api/files/{clean_path}` where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n- **Headers:** `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- **Stream:** `True` (for efficient large file download)\n- **Body:** Writes response content to local file\n\n**List Files:**\n```python\ndef list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n    \"\"\"List files in remote path.\n\n    Args:\n        path: Remote path (default: \".\")\n\n    Returns:\n        Directory listing structure\n\n    Raises:\n        DataPlaneError: On list failure\n    \"\"\"\n```\n- **Method:** `GET`\n- **Path:** `api/files?path={path}`\n- **Headers:** `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- **Response:** JSON with directory contents\n\n#### Code Execution\n\n```python\ndef run_code(\n    self,\n    language: str,\n    code: str,\n    timeout: Optional[float] = None\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Execute code in specified language.\n\n    Args:\n        language: Programming language (python, python3, py)\n        code: Code to execute\n        timeout: Execution timeout in seconds\n\n    Returns:\n        Code execution output\n\n    Note:\n        For Python, writes timestamped .py file and executes via execute_command\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Python Code Path:**\n1. Check if language is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n2. Generate timestamped filename: `code_{timestamp}.py`\n3. Call `write_file(code, filename)`\n4. Call `execute_command([\"python3\", filename], timeout)`\n5. Return output\n\n### 6. AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n\n#### Class Structure\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ):\n        \"\"\"Initialize Agent Runtime data plane client.\n\n        Args:\n            router_url: Router base URL\n            namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n            agent_name: Agent name\n            timeout: Read timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n            connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n            pool_connections: Connection pool size (default: 10)\n            pool_maxsize: Max connections per pool (default: 10)\n        \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Base URL Construction:**\n```python\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n**Session Configuration:**\n- Creates session with connection pooling\n- Sets default header: `{SESSION_HEADER}: {session_id}`\n\n#### Session Bootstrap\n\n```python\ndef bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Bootstrap session ID from Agent Runtime endpoint.\n\n    Returns:\n        Session ID from response header\n\n    Raises:\n        ValueError: If session_id header not present\n        requests.exceptions.RequestException: On HTTP errors\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**HTTP Details:**\n- **Method:** `GET`\n- **Path:** `self.base_url` (full invocation URL)\n- **Headers:** None (session not yet known)\n- **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n- **Response Processing:**\n  - Read `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n  - Raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` if missing\n  - Return session ID\n\n#### Agent Invocation\n\n```python\ndef invoke(\n    self,\n    session_id: str,\n    payload: Dict[str, Any],\n    timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n) -> requests.Response:\n    \"\"\"Invoke agent with payload.\n\n    Args:\n        session_id: Session ID for header\n        payload: Agent invocation payload (JSON-serializable)\n        timeout: Request timeout in seconds (None for default)\n\n    Returns:\n        requests.Response object\n\n    Raises:\n        ValueError: If session_id is falsy\n        requests.exceptions.RequestException: On HTTP errors\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**HTTP Details:**\n- **Method:** `POST`\n- **Path:** `self.base_url`\n- **Headers:** `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n- **Body:** JSON payload\n- **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout_value or self.timeout)`\n- **Validation:** Raises `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` if session_id falsy\n\n### 7. High-Level Clients\n\n#### CodeInterpreterClient\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n    ):\n        \"\"\"Initialize Code Interpreter client.\n\n        Args:\n            name: Session name\n            namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n            ttl: Session time-to-live in seconds\n            workload_manager_url: Workload Manager URL\n            router_url: Router URL (required, or ROUTER_URL env var)\n            auth_token: Authentication token\n            verbose: Enable verbose logging\n            session_id: Existing session ID (skip creation if provided)\n        \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Initialization Flow:**\n1. Validate `router_url` (raise ValueError if missing)\n2. Store configuration\n3. Create logger\n4. Initialize `ControlPlaneClient`\n5. If `session_id` not provided:\n   - Call `create_session()` via control plane\n   - Store new session ID\n6. Call `_init_data_plane()` to create data plane client\n\n**Context Manager:**\n```python\ndef __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\":\n    return self\n\ndef __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n    self.stop()\n```\n\n**Stop/Cleanup:**\n```python\ndef stop(self) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Stop Code Interpreter session.\n\n    Closes data plane, deletes control plane session (if created),\n    and closes control plane HTTP session.\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Delegate Methods:**\n- `execute_command(command, timeout)` → data plane\n- `run_code(language, code, timeout)` → data plane\n- `write_file(content, remote_path)` → data plane\n- `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` → data plane\n- `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` → data plane\n- `list_files(path)` → data plane\n\n#### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    ):\n        \"\"\"Initialize Agent Runtime client.\n\n        Args:\n            agent_name: Agent name\n            namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n            router_url: Router URL (or ROUTER_URL env var)\n            verbose: Enable verbose logging\n            session_id: Existing session ID\n            timeout: Default request timeout\n            connect_timeout: Connect timeout\n        \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Initialization Flow:**\n1. Store configuration\n2. Create logger\n3. Initialize `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n4. If `session_id` not provided:\n   - Call `bootstrap_session_id()` to get session from endpoint\n   - Store new session ID\n\n**Context Manager:**\n```python\ndef __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\":\n    return self\n\ndef __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n    self.close()\n```\n\n**Invoke:**\n```python\ndef invoke(\n    self,\n    payload: Dict[str, Any],\n    timeout: Optional[float] = None\n) -> Any:\n    \"\"\"Invoke agent with payload.\n\n    Args:\n        payload: Agent invocation payload\n        timeout: Request timeout (None for default)\n\n    Returns:\n        Agent response\n\n    Raises:\n        ValueError: If session_id not initialized\n        requests.exceptions.RequestException: On HTTP errors\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Close:**\n```python\ndef close(self) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Close HTTP session and release resources.\"\"\"\n    self.dp_client.close()\n```\n\n### 8. Exception Hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when command execution fails with non-zero exit code.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail.\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n**Exception Usage:**\n- `CommandExecutionError`: Raised by `execute_command()` on non-zero exit\n- `SessionError`: Defined for extension (not currently raised by core)\n- `DataPlaneError`: Defined for extension (not currently raised by core)\n- `ValueError`: Used for invalid configuration (e.g., missing URLs)\n- `requests.exceptions`: Used for HTTP errors\n\n### 9. Configuration Resolution\n\n#### ControlPlaneClient Configuration\n\n| Setting | Resolution Order | Default |\n|---------|-----------------|---------|\n| `base_url` | `workload_manager_url` → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Required |\n| `Authorization` | `auth_token` → `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` | Optional |\n| `timeout` | Constructor parameter | 120 |\n| `connect_timeout` | Constructor parameter | 5.0 |\n| `pool_connections` | Constructor parameter | 10 |\n| `pool_maxsize` | Constructor parameter | 10 |\n\n#### CodeInterpreterClient Configuration\n\n| Setting | Resolution Order | Default |\n|---------|-----------------|---------|\n| `router_url` | Constructor → `ROUTER_URL` | Required |\n| `workload_manager_url` | Constructor → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Optional |\n| `auth_token` | Constructor → SA token file | Optional |\n| `name` | Constructor | \"my-interpreter\" |\n| `namespace` | Constructor | \"default\" |\n| `ttl` | Constructor | 3600 |\n| `verbose` | Constructor | False |\n| `session_id` | Constructor (skip creation) | Auto-created |\n| `timeout` | Constructor | 120 |\n| `connect_timeout` | Constructor | 5.0 |\n\n#### AgentRuntimeClient Configuration\n\n| Setting | Resolution Order | Default |\n|---------|-----------------|---------|\n| `router_url` | Constructor → `ROUTER_URL` | Required |\n| `agent_name` | Constructor | Required |\n| `namespace` | Constructor | \"default\" |\n| `verbose` | Constructor | False |\n| `session_id` | Constructor (skip bootstrap) | Auto-bootstrapped |\n| `timeout` | Constructor | 120 |\n| `connect_timeout` | Constructor | 5.0 |\n\n## HTTP API Contracts\n\n### Control Plane API\n\n#### Create Session\n\n```http\nPOST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter\nContent-Type: application/json\nAuthorization: Bearer {token}\n\n{\n  \"name\": \"my-interpreter\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"ttl\": 3600,\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"key\": \"value\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"abc123def456\"\n}\n```\n\n#### Delete Session\n\n```http\nDELETE {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}\nContent-Type: application/json\nAuthorization: Bearer {token}\n```\n\n**Response:** 200 OK or 404 Not Found\n\n### Code Interpreter Data Plane API\n\n#### Execute Command\n\n```http\nPOST {base_url}/api/execute\nx-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\n  \"command\": [\"python3\", \"script.py\"],\n  \"timeout\": \"60s\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"exit_code\": 0,\n  \"stdout\": \"output\",\n  \"stderr\": \"error output\"\n}\n```\n\n#### Write File\n\n```http\nPOST {base_url}/api/files\nx-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\n  \"path\": \"/path/to/file.txt\",\n  \"content\": \"SGVsbG8gV29ybGQ=\",  // base64 encoded\n  \"mode\": \"0644\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response:** 200 OK\n\n#### Upload File\n\n```http\nPOST {base_url}/api/files\nx-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n\nContent-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary\n\n------WebKitFormBoundary\nContent-Disposition: form-data; name=\"file\"; filename=\"local.txt\"\nContent-Type: application/octet-stream\n\n[file contents]\n------WebKitFormBoundary\nContent-Disposition: form-data; name=\"path\"\n\n/path/to/remote.txt\n------WebKitFormBoundary\nContent-Disposition: form-data; name=\"mode\"\n\n0644\n------WebKitFormBoundary--\n```\n\n**Response:** 200 OK\n\n#### Download File\n\n```http\nGET {base_url}/api/files/path/to/file.txt\nx-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n```\n\n**Response:** File content streamed\n\n#### List Files\n\n```http\nGET {base_url}/api/files?path=/path\nx-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\"name\": \"file1.txt\", \"size\": 1024, \"mode\": \"0644\"},\n    {\"name\": \"file2.py\", \"size\": 2048, \"mode\": \"0755\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Agent Runtime Data Plane API\n\n#### Bootstrap Session\n\n```http\nGET {base_url}\n```\n\n**Response Headers:**\n```\nx-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n```\n\n#### Invoke Agent\n\n```http\nPOST {base_url}\nx-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\n  \"input\": \"user input\",\n  \"context\": {}\n}\n```\n\n**Response:** Agent-specific JSON response\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Runtime Dependencies (`pyproject.toml`)\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography\",\n]\n```\n\n**Dependency Details:**\n- `requests`: HTTP client library for API communication\n- `PyJWT>=2.0.0`: JWT token handling (for future JWT-based auth)\n- `cryptography`: Cryptographic utilities (for JWT operations)\n\n### Build Configuration\n\n```toml\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n\n[tool.setuptools]\npackages = [\"agentcube\"]\n\n[tool.setuptools.package-data]\nagentcube = [\"py.typed\"]\n```\n\n**Package Configuration:**\n- Minimum Python: 3.10\n- Build system: setuptools\n- Package inclusion: All `agentcube*` files\n- Type hints included for better IDE support\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests Required\n\n| Component | Test Cases |\n|-----------|------------|\n| `create_session()` | - Session creation with default pooling<br>- Custom pool sizes<br>- HTTPAdapter mounted for both http/https |\n| `read_token_from_file()` | - Read existing token file<br>- FileNotFoundError returns empty string<br>- Whitespace stripping |\n| `get_logger()` | - Logger creation with default level<br>- Custom level (int and string)<br>- Logger name propagation |\n| `ControlPlaneClient.__init__()` | - URL resolution from parameter and env<br>- Token resolution from parameter and file<br>- Session header configuration<br>- Missing required URL |\n| `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` | - Successful session creation<br>- Extract sessionId from response<br>- Missing sessionId raises ValueError<br>- HTTP errors propagate |\n| `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` | - Successful deletion (200)<br>- 404 treated as success<br>- Other errors logged and return False |\n| `ControlPlaneClient.close()` | - Session cleanup |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.__init__()` | - Base URL construction from components<br>- Base URL override<br>- Session header configuration |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command()` | - Successful command execution<br>- Non-zero exit raises CommandExecutionError<br>- Timeout buffer calculation<br>- Command string and list handling |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.write_file()` | - Base64 encoding<br>- Successful write<br>- HTTP errors propagate |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.upload_file()` | - Multipart form construction<br>- Session header on upload<br>- File not found raises FileNotFoundError |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.download_file()` | - Streaming download<br>- Path cleaning (lstrip)<br>- File writing |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.list_files()` | - Query parameter construction<br>- Successful list<br>- HTTP errors propagate |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__()` | - Base URL construction<br>- Session header constant |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()` | - Successful bootstrap<br>- Missing header raises ValueError<br>- HTTP errors propagate |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke()` | - Successful invocation<br>- Missing session_id raises ValueError<br>- Timeout handling<br>- JSON serialization |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__()` | - Missing router_url raises ValueError<br>- Session creation via control plane<br>- Existing session_id reuse<br>- Data plane init failure cleanup |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient.__enter__/__exit__()` | - Context manager protocol<br>- stop() called on exit |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient.stop()` | - Data plane closure<br>- Session deletion (if created)<br>- Control plane closure |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient.execute_command()` | - Delegation to data plane<br>- CommandExecutionError propagation |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient.run_code()` | - Python code path (write + execute)<br>- Other languages via data plane |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__()` | - Session bootstrap when not provided<br>- Existing session_id reuse |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` | - Delegation to data plane<br>- Timeout handling |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient.__enter__/__exit__()` | - Context manager protocol<br>- close() called on exit |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Scenario | Test Cases |\n|----------|------------|\n| End-to-end Code Interpreter | - Full session lifecycle<br>- Multiple operations<br>- Error recovery |\n| End-to-end Agent Runtime | - Session bootstrap<br>- Multiple invocations<br>- Timeout handling |\n| Concurrent clients | - Multiple clients sharing connection pool<br>- Pool exhaustion handling |\n| Network resilience | - Retry on transient failures<br>- Timeout behavior<br)- Connection pool reuse |\n\n### Mock Tests\n\n- Mock `requests.Session` for HTTP calls\n- Mock `ControlPlaneClient` in high-level clients\n- Mock file I/O for token reading\n- Mock logger for testing without side effects\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Token Handling:**\n   - Tokens are read from K8s service account files in production\n   - Tokens are never logged or exposed in error messages\n   - Token file permissions should be 0600\n\n2. **URL Validation:**\n   - Validate URL format before use\n   - Prevent URL injection attacks\n   - Use HTTPS in production\n\n3. **Header Management:**\n   - Session headers are case-sensitive: `x-agentcube-session-id`\n   - Headers are properly sanitized before use\n\n4. **Path Security:**\n   - File paths are sanitized before API calls\n   - Path traversal prevented with `lstrip(\"/\")` for downloads\n\n5. **Connection Pooling:**\n   - Pool size limits prevent resource exhaustion\n   - Connections are properly closed on cleanup\n\n6. **Timeout Configuration:**\n   - Timeouts prevent hanging requests\n   - Connect and read timeouts are separate\n\n7. **Error Messages:**\n   - Sensitive data not included in error messages\n   - Stack traces only in verbose mode\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n1. **Connection Pooling:**\n   - Reuses connections for multiple requests\n   - Reduces TCP/TLS handshake overhead\n   - Configurable pool sizes\n\n2. **Timeout Management:**\n   - Separate connect and read timeouts\n   - Per-call timeout overrides\n   - Timeout buffer for long-running commands\n\n3. **Streaming Downloads:**\n   - Large files streamed to memory\n   - Prevents memory exhaustion\n   - Efficient for big file downloads\n\n4. **Session Reuse:**\n   - HTTP session created once per client\n   - Headers configured once\n   - Reduced overhead for repeated calls\n\n5. **Multipart Uploads:**\n   - Efficient file upload mechanism\n   - Minimal memory overhead\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Retry Logic:**\n   - Configurable retry on transient failures\n   - Exponential backoff\n   - Retry-specific exceptions\n\n2. **Request Signing:**\n   - JWT-based authentication\n   - Request signature verification\n   - Token refresh mechanism\n\n3. **Metrics Collection:**\n   - Request latency tracking\n   - Error rate monitoring\n   - Connection pool metrics\n\n4. **Circuit Breaker:**\n   - Prevent cascading failures\n   - Automatic recovery\n   - Configurable thresholds\n\n5. **Async Support:**\n   - `aiohttp` integration\n   - Async context managers\n   - Non-blocking I/O\n\n6. **Advanced Logging:**\n   - Request/response logging\n   - Structured logging (JSON)\n   - Log correlation IDs\n\n7. **WebSocket Support:**\n   - Real-time communication\n   - Streaming responses\n   - Keepalive handling\n\n8. **Custom Adapters:**\n   - Pluggable HTTP adapters\n   - Custom retry strategies\n   - Advanced connection management","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/python-sdk/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/python-sdk/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/python-sdk/design.md","time":{"start":1775879630941,"end":1775879631092}}}}
